style.text:
^[%[
](4)](center)^[%[Turning your operational data](4)](center)^[%[into insights and action](4)](center)

%[The **_24\-Hour Summary_** provides an overview of system performance during the 24 hours prior to the latest reload. The tables and charts help answer questions about your environment.](2)
%[
**Key Performance Indicators \(KPIs\)**](2)
^[%[> Do any KPIs for the last 24 hours stand out?](2)](left)^[%[\- Max CPU](2)](left)^[%[\- Max RAM](2)](left)^[%[\- Reloads, Failures](2)](left)^[%[\- Avg Reload Duration, Max](2)](left)^[%[\- Max Concurrent Users, Apps](2)](left)^[%[\- Errors, Warnings**
**](2)](left)^[**%[Overview](2)**](left)^[%[> How does performance during the last 24 hours compare with the last 7 or 28 days?](2)](left)^[%[**Last 24 Hours of Activity**
> Are there any hours that show high levels of activity \(users, reloads, etc.\) that might be correlated to errors, high CPU, or high RAM?](2)](left)

%[**_Performance _**presents trend charts and details of performance metrics over time.](2)
^[%[
**Qlik Sense Server CPU**](2)](left)^[%[> Are there periods or patterns of peak CPU usage? If so, what is the Qlik Sense Server RAM usage during those periods?](2)](left)^[%[**Qlik Sense Server RAM**
> Are there periods or patterns of peak RAM usage? If so, what else is happening during those periods?](2)](left)^[%[**Concurrent Users & Apps**
> What are the trends for concurrent users & concurrent \(open\) apps over time? Are the high activity periods causing problems reflected in RAM or CPU usage?](2)](left)^[**%[Performance Summary](2)**](left)^[%[> Do this table's details illuminate issues observed in the charts above?](2)](left)^[%[> Are there hours during each day that exhibit high activity or load?](2)](left)

%[**_Ta__sk Overview _**gives a high\-level view of reload task history.](2)
^[
**%[Task Key Performance Indicators \(KPIs\)](2)**](left)^[%[_These KPIs provide a quick read on overall reload status._](2)](left)^[**%[Reload Count](2)**](left)^[%[> Do certain reloads display high frequency of failures \(red\)?](2)](left)^[%[**R****eloads by Hour**](2)](left)^[%[> When are peak reload times?](2)](left)^[%[> Are there "off\-hour" times when more reloads could be executed?](2)
**%[Reload ](2)****%[Count and Duration Trend](2)**%[
> Are reloads taking longer than expected? Are they increasing over time?](2)](left)^[%[> Do certain dates exhibit longer\-than\-average reload times?](2)](left)

%[**_Task Details _**displays more detailed history of all reloads.](2)
^[
**%[Reload Summary Statistics](2)**](left)^[%[> Which tasks have a high failure rate?](2)](left)^[%[> Which tasks historically take longest?](2)](left)^[%[> Do any apps have more than one associated reload task?](2)](left)^[%[> Have any reload tasks not been executed for a long time?
](2)](left)^[%[**ReloadDetails**
> What other task reloads are executing at the same time a certain reloadfailure occurs?](2)](left)

%[**_Session Overview_** gives an overview session activity.](2)

^[**%[Key Performance Indicators \(KPIs\)](2)**](left)^[_%[These KPIs provide a quick read on overall session activity.](2)_](left)^[**%[Top 10 Apps](2)**](left)^[%[> What are the most accessedapps?](2)](left)^[**%[Top 10 Users](2)**](left)^[%[> Who are the top users?
**Reloads by Hour**](2)](left)^[%[> When are peak session times?](2)](left)^[%[> Are there specific hours with high activity that might conflict with reloads or other service activity?
**User and App Count Trend**
> Are more users accessing apps over time?](2)](left)^[%[> Are there any cyclic usage patterns over time?](2)](left)

%[**_Session Details_** presents a more detailed history of sessions.](2)
^[
**%[App Session Summary](2)**](left)^[%[> Do certain apps have high session counts but low user counts?](2)](left)^[%[> Are there any apps that have not been used recently?](2)](left)^[**%[User Session Summary](2)**](left)^[%[> Are some users accessing a large number of apps?](2)](left)^[%[> Do some users open apps for only short sessions?](2)](left)^[%[**Session Details**
> Are there apps or users that consistently exhibit long durations? ](2)](left)^[%[> What could these session statistics indicate about app content or design?](2)](left)

%[**_QMC Change Log _**presents information about select changes made to resources in the QMC, including Apps, Streams, and Users.](2)
^[%[
**Change Summary**](2)](left)^[%[> How many changes have been made to each Resource Type?](2)](left)^[%[> Who was the last person to make a change to each Resource Type?](2)](left)^[**%[Change Users](2)**](left)^[%[> Which QMC users are making the most changes?](2)](left)^[%[> Are changes being made by QMC users who should not have Admin privileges?](2)](left)^[**%[QMC Change Log](2)**](left)^[%[> How have Security Rules been changed?](2)](left)^[%[> Have any apps or content been added, published, or exported inappropriately?](2)](left)

The **Dimensions**, **Measures**, and **Visualizations **in this app's _**#[Master Library](3)**_ enable customized analysis of your Qlik site \- especially helpful for multi\-node deployments.Consider some of the possibilities...

%[**_Ta__sk Planning_** presents views into task reload history and task inter\-dependency to capacity planning analysis.](2)
^[
**%[Reload Heatmap: Reload Count](2)**](left)^[%[> Are certain hours of certain days of the week overly busy?](2)](left)^[%[> Could any reload tasks be scheduled from busy times to less busy hours?](2)](left)^[**%[Reload Heatmap: Reload CPU Spent](2)**](left)^[%[> Do certain hours of certain day exhibit high levels of CPU utilization for reloads?](2)](left)^[%[> Could any high\-CPU reload tasks be scheduled differently to level out CPU during the week?](2)](left)^[**%[Task Chains: Paths](2)**](left)^[%[This table lists all the possible task chain paths, some of which may overlap.](2)](left)^[%[> Are there any unexpected "high depth" task chains that could be simplified?](2)](left)^[%[**Task Chain: Median Reload Duration**
This chart shows the median reload duration of all tasks which follow the Task in the left\-hand column.](2)](left)^[%[> Do certain task chains show long total reload duration?](2)](left)^[%[> Which tasks in these task chains are contributing to long reload duration?](2)](left)

qMetaDef.title: Users per Hour
qMetaDef.description: Average number of users accessing apps per hour.

qMetaDef.title: Avg Session Duration
qMetaDef.description: Average session duration, given in fraction of days. Use the "Duration" number format.

qMetaDef.title: Avg KB Transferred
qMetaDef.description: Represents the average quantity of data sent and received for user sessions, given in KB.

qMetaDef.title: KB Transferred
qMetaDef.description: Represents the quantity of data sent and received during a user session, given in KB.

qMetaDef.title: Cache Miss Rate
qMetaDef.description: A measure of how many cache results have been cached.  A high miss rate means the cache is not being used effectively.Clearing the cache periodically will of course result in the miss rate rising (and then recovering).

qMetaDef.title: Avg Selections
qMetaDef.description: Average number of selections made in user sessions.

qMetaDef.title: Apps
qMetaDef.description: Printing/Exporting from Apps: Count of unique Apps from which app objects were printed/exported by users.

qMetaDef.title: Last Reload Failure
qMetaDef.description: Time of the last Reload failure.

qMetaDef.title: Avg Export Duration
qMetaDef.description:
Average length of time to complete an export of an app object. In other words, how much time passed between the moment a user clicked "Export object to PDF" and the resulting pdf was saved.
Use the interval number format.

qMetaDef.title: Last Reload Success
qMetaDef.description: Time of the last Reload success.

qMetaDef.title: Reloads per Hour
qMetaDef.description: Task reloads per hour.

qMetaDef.title: Reloads
qMetaDef.description: Count of task reloads initiated in the QMC.

qMetaDef.title: CPU Above 95%
qMetaDef.description: Percentage of time the Qlik Sense process CPU exceeds 95%.

qMetaDef.title: Exports
qMetaDef.description: Count of app object exports (for example "Export chart to PDF").

qMetaDef.title: Apps
qMetaDef.description: SESSION Apps: Count of unique Apps accessed by users.

qMetaDef.title: Export Errors
qMetaDef.description: Errors encountered when attempting to export an app object, for example "Export story to Pptx".

qMetaDef.title: Apps Accessed per Day
qMetaDef.description: Average number of unique apps opened per day.

qMetaDef.title: Session Duration
qMetaDef.description:
Duration of a  user-app session.
Use the interval number format.

qMetaDef.title: Reload Duration
qMetaDef.description: The standard deviation () of reload duration.

qMetaDef.title: Cache Bytes Added
qMetaDef.description: This is the total in-memory size of the result and data added to the cache during the period. This measures how the volume of new results, and can be used to judge if increased memory consumption is caused by request or by traffic e.g. When the memory is saturated (7090% default), a corresponding volume of results are dropped from the cache.

qMetaDef.title: Errors & Warnings
qMetaDef.description: 24 Hours: Errors and Warnings generated in prior 24 hours (based on selections).

qMetaDef.title: Cache Hits
qMetaDef.description: Cache hits is the number of lookups of results or sub-results in the Engines result and data cache that was hit (found), and thus re-used without needing calculation. Not all stages of a given task uses the cache and usually needs some additional processing before the result is complete, so even Cache hits result in some load on the machine.

qMetaDef.title: CPU Spent (ms)
qMetaDef.description: Count of CPU spent during user sessions, given in milliseconds (ms).

qMetaDef.title: Max KB Transferred
qMetaDef.description: Represents the max quantity of data sent and received during a user session, given in KB.

qMetaDef.title: Export Duration
qMetaDef.description:
Duration of  export of app object. In other words, how much time passed between the time a user clicked "Export object to PDF" and the resulting pdf was saved.
Use the interval number format.

qMetaDef.title: QMC Changes
qMetaDef.description: Count of changes made in the QMC.

qMetaDef.title: Users
qMetaDef.description: Export & Print Users: Count of unique users who exported an app object from a Sense app.

qMetaDef.title: Last Reload
qMetaDef.description: Time of the last Reload execution.

qMetaDef.title: Max CPU Spent (ms)
qMetaDef.description: Max count of CPU spent for a user session, given in milliseconds (ms).

qMetaDef.title: Avg CPU Spent (ms)
qMetaDef.description: Average count of CPU spent across user sessions, given in milliseconds (ms).

qMetaDef.title: Reload Failures
qMetaDef.description: 24 Hours: Count of Task Reloads during last 24 hours.

qMetaDef.title: Cache Hit Rate
qMetaDef.description: Percent of Cache Lookups resulting in a successful Hit (find). A measure of how many cache results have been cached.  A high hit rate means the cache is being used effectively. Under most circumstances this is to be expected. Clearing the cache periodically will of course result in the hit rate dropping (and then recovering).

qMetaDef.title: Reloads
qMetaDef.description: 24 Hours: Count of Task Reloads during last 24 hours.

qMetaDef.title: Selections
qMetaDef.description: Count of selections made in user session.

qMetaDef.title: Avg Reload Duration
qMetaDef.description: User Duration number format.

qMetaDef.title: Reloads per Day
qMetaDef.description: Count of task reload execution per day.

qMetaDef.title: Apps per Hour
qMetaDef.description: Average number of apps opened and accessed per hour.

qMetaDef.title: Max Concurrent Apps
qMetaDef.description: Maximum number of apps open concurrently.

qMeasure.qDef: count({<[Session Count]={1}>} DISTINCT UserId)/count({<[Session Count]={1}>} DISTINCT Date)

qMetaDef.title: Users per Day
qMetaDef.description: Average count of users accessing apps per day.

qMetaDef.title: Users
qMetaDef.description: SESSION Users: Count of unique users who accessed a Sense app.

qMetaDef.title: Days Since Last Session
qMetaDef.description: Number of days since the last session with the app.

variables.qDefinition:
ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId as _proxySessionPackage,
  										If(Command='Open app:LoadObjects',0) as [Session Count],'0.0000'& rowno() as Sequence#,applymap('qmc_change_map',subfield(Command,' ',1),null()) as qmc_change,IF(applymap('qmc_change_map',subfield(Command,' ',1),null())=1
                                        	and substringcount(Command,':')=0,
        									IF(left(UserId,3)<>'sa_' and UserId <> 'Not available' and UserId <> 'System',
                                               upper(left(mid(Command,Index(Command,' ')+1),1))&mid(mid(Command,Index(Command,' ')+1),2) 
                                               	)) as [QMC Resource Type],UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

applymap('qmc_change_map',subfield(Command,' ',1),null()) as qmc_change,IF(applymap('qmc_change_map',subfield(Command,' ',1),null())=1
                                        	and substringcount(Command,':')=0,
        									IF(left(UserId,3)<>'sa_' and UserId <> 'Not available' and UserId <> 'System',
                                               upper(left(mid(Command,Index(Command,' ')+1),1))&mid(mid(Command,Index(Command,' ')+1),2) 
                                               	)) as [QMC Resource Type],

'Synchronization' as Command,
  										subfield(Logger,'.',-1) as Description,
                                        '0' as ProxySessionId,
  										Id as _proxySessionPackage,
                                        'Repository' as Service,
                                        Level as Severity,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname

RequestSequenceId as _proxySessionPackage,
  										Index(Command,'Export') as [Export Count],
                                        Index(Command,'Store') as [Export Store Count],UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId as _proxySessionPackage,
  											If(Context='Doc::DoReload',1) as [Reload from Hub],
                                        	If(Context='Doc::DoReload',1) as TaskExecution,
                                            If(Context='Doc::DoReload',ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId&RequestSequenceId) as TaskId,UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId as _proxySessionPackage,
  										If(Message='Changing task state to Triggered',0,
  												IF(Message like 'Task finished*',1,
                                                	IF(Result <> 30 AND Result>=20 AND Result <45,1))) as TaskExecution,
                                         subfield(ObjectId,'|',1) as TaskId,UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

'Synchronization' as Command,
  										subfield(Logger,'.',-1) as Description,
                                        '0' as ProxySessionId,
  										Id as _proxySessionPackage,
                                        'Repository' as Service,
                                        Level as Severity,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname

ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId as _proxySessionPackage,
                                         Selections as [Session Selections],
                                         If(ProxySessionId='0',null(), round([CPU Spent (s)]*1000,0.01)) 		as [Session CPU Spent (ms)],
                                         If(ProxySessionId='0',round([CPU Spent (s)]*1000,0.01)) 				as [Reload CPU Spent (ms)],
                                         If(ProxySessionId='0',null(),ceil(("Bytes Received"+"Bytes Sent")/1024)) as [Session KBytes Sent+Received],
                                         If(ProxySessionId='0',ceil(("Bytes Received"+"Bytes Sent")/1024)) 	as [Reload KBytes Sent+Received],
                                         AppId as ObjectId

ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId as _proxySessionPackage,
  										If(Command='Close connection',1) as [Session Count],UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId as _proxySessionPackage,SecurityClass, ClientHostAddress,'0.0000'& rowno() as Sequence#,applymap('qmc_change_map',subfield(Command,' ',1),null()) as qmc_change,IF(applymap('qmc_change_map',subfield(Command,' ',1),null())=1
                                        	and substringcount(Command,':')=0,
        									IF(left(UserId,3)<>'sa_' and UserId <> 'Not available' and UserId <> 'System',
                                               upper(left(mid(Command,Index(Command,' ')+1),1))&mid(mid(Command,Index(Command,' ')+1),2) 
                                               	)) as [QMC Resource Type],UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId as _proxySessionPackage,SecurityClass, ClientHostAddress,UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

Severity,If(ProxyPackageId=0 AND ProxySessionId=0, Id, ProxySessionId&ProxyPackageId) as _proxySessionPackage,UserDirectory & chr(92) & UserId as UserId,
  										ObjectId,ObjectName,
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname,
                                        Service,
                                        ProxySessionId,ProxyPackageId,RequestSequenceId,
  										Context,Command,Result,Description,
                                        if(ObjectName ='Not available',null(),
                                        	IF(Service='Scheduler',subfield(ObjectName,'|',2),
                                            	IF(Service='Printing' and Index(Command,'Export'),subfield(ObjectName,'|',-1),
                                        			IF(right(Command,3)='app' OR Context like '*/app/*',ObjectName))
                                        	)) AS [App Name],
  										ProductVersion

ActiveDocSessions,ActiveDocs,ActiveUsers,CPULoad/100 as CPULoad,LoadedDocs,Selections,
										Round("VMCommitted(MB)"/1024,0.01) as VMCommitted,
                                        Round("VMAllocated(MB)"/1024,0.01) as VMAllocated,
    									Round("VMFree(MB)"/1024,0.01) as VMFree,
                                        round("VMCommitted(MB)"/("VMFree(MB)"+"VMCommitted(MB)"),0.01) as VMPctCommitted,
                                        Id as _proxySessionPackage,
                                        'Engine' as Service,
                                        Level as Severity,
                                        CacheHits as [Cache Hits],CacheLookups as [Cache Lookups],CacheBytesAdded as [Cache Bytes Added],
                                        lower(Hostname) as Hostname
